        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 2:57PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles north of Basin, or 15 miles northwest of
Boulder, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena, East Helena, Montana City, Wickes, Rimini, Alhambra, Spring
Meadow Lake State Park, Corbin, Clancy, Austin, and Jefferson City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
